<subSubSection pageId="117" pageNumber="513" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="117.[114,1322,1127,2057]" pageId="117" pageNumber="513">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[116,464,1792,1821]" pageId="117" pageNumber="513">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Data Deficient on The IUCN Red List. The Ugandan Lowland White-toothed Shrew is relatively common throughoutits range. It may be threatened by habitat destruction and fragmentation, especially in Kenya. The species is found in the Mabira Forest Reserve in Uganda, although this reserve is currently threatened with timber extraction.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
